title: Generative AI Summer Analyst
description:
Passionate about precision medicine and advancing the healthcare industry?
Recent advancements in underlying technology have finally made it possible for AI to impact clinical care in a meaningful way. Tempus' proprietary platform connects an entire ecosystem of real-world evidence to deliver real-time, actionable insights to physicians, providing critical information about the right treatments for the right patients, at the right time.
Tempus is seeking a highly qualified undergraduate Generative AI Summer Analyst to work with us for the summer of 2025. We are looking for people who can change the world.
Our goal is to provide you with a comprehensive overview of what it‚Äôs like to work at Tempus and the chance to have a true impact. We hope that at the end of your internship, you leave with a deeper understanding and appreciation for Tempus‚Äô profound goals and mission;¬† to connect an entire ecosystem of real-world evidence to deliver real-time, actionable insights to physicians, providing critical information about the right treatments for the right patients, at the right time.
As a Summer Intern at Tempus, you will:

Apply skills and knowledge learned in the classroom to on-the-job experiences
Work on comprehensive, value-added project(s) that help enhance the fields of science and technology¬†
Collaborate with teams/colleagues in a fast-paced environment¬†
Gain professional development & build relationships with peers from across the country¬†

Anticipated Summer Project(s):

Project #1: Supporting White-Glove Agent Development

Collaborate with business units and leaders to develop custom AI Agents.
Iterate and improve Agents based on feedback and performance metrics
Facilitate cross-functional communication and collaboration for successful Agent development.
Provide best practices & technical support to external partners in building and deploying AI Agents.



Project #2: Gen AI Commercial Go-To-Market (GTM) Efforts

Conduct market research to identify potential partners and customers.
Develop and refine GTM strategies for Tempus OS, Agent Builder, David, and Tempus One.
Engage with partners and customers, presenting and demonstrating Tempus AI's solutions.
Support integration of Gen AI solutions within EHRs and other healthcare systems.

Project #3: Gen AI Evangelism and Thought Leadership

Create and publish engaging content (blogs, whitepapers, case studies) on AI in precision medicine.
Develop and execute social media campaigns to promote Tempus AI's innovations.
Collaborate with the marketing team on strategies to enhance brand recognition and Gen AI adoption.


Qualifications:

Pursuing a Bachelor's degree in Biological Sciences, Biotechnology, or a related field
Strong interest in pursuing an MD/PhD program with a focus on leveraging technology and data science in healthcare.
Proficiency in data analysis tools such as R, Python, and Excel.
Collaboration: Working effectively with cross-functional teams and external partners.
Problem-Solving: Identifying issues and developing solutions to improve AI Agents.
Adaptability: Flexibility in adjusting to new information, changing conditions, or unexpected obstacles.
Communication: Clearly conveying ideas and information to team members and stakeholders.
Time Management: Balancing multiple tasks and meeting deadlines effectively.
Excellent written and verbal communication skills in a variety of settings and media.
Strong computer skills, including advanced knowledge of Google Suite and Gmail, preferred.
A self-starter with the ability to work independently as well as in collaboration with others in a fast-paced environment is critical. Be ready to fly the plane as you‚Äôre still building it!

Additional Details:

You will spend 8 or 10 weeks working in our Chicago office. The internship will be a hybrid, onsite 3 days/week with the option to work remotely the remaining days.
The program will start in early June and run through August.
A competitive hourly wage will be provided for the summer employment and a relocation bonus to help offset some of the relocation costs and resources to help you find housing.

Additionally,¬†for remote roles open to individuals in unincorporated Los Angeles ‚Äì including remote roles-¬†Tempus reasonably believes that criminal history may have a direct, adverse and negative relationship on the following job duties, potentially resulting in the withdrawal of the conditional offer of employment: engaging positively with customers and other employees; accessing confidential information, including intellectual property, trade secrets, and protected health information; and appropriately handling such information in accordance with legal and ethical standards. Qualified applicants with arrest or conviction records will be considered for employment in accordance with applicable law, including the Los Angeles County Fair Chance Ordinance for Employers and the California Fair Chance Act.
